article.headline: Troy State 76, Central Florida 64
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Rob Lewin scored 18 points and Troy State snapped Central Florida's 14-game winning streak with a 76-64 win Saturday night in front of the first-ever sellout crowd at UCF Arena. Herbert Davis added 13 points and Greg Davis finished with 10 points for Troy State (14-5, 10-2 Atlantic Sun). The Trojans avenged a two-point loss to the Golden Knights on their home court and handed UCF its first defeat since Dec. 4. UCF (16-3, 11-1) whittled a 16-point halftime deficit to 55-44 with 9:30 remaining, but three-pointers by reserves Corey Hornsby and Ryan Heck pushed the Trojans lead back to 17. The Golden Knights never recovered. The top 3-point shooting team in the league, Troy State hit 10 from long range. The Golden Knights have scored less than 60 points in two of its three losses this season. Dexter Lyons led UCF with 21 points while Roberto Morentin and Josh Bodden each had 12 points. In the first half, the Trojans held the Golden Knights to one field goal over a seven-minute span and caused numerous turnovers on their way to a 26-9 run and a 30-18 lead. Troy State hit 6-of-10 three-pointers in the first half and led 40-24 at halftime.
